PAMEx Demo:

1) Show the language file for test11
2) Run test11 through the parser
	- name the level database leveldb
	- name the output policy-out
3) Show the policy-out and leveldb files
4) Run the fludb tool with policy-out
	- use /etc/userdb for the userdb location
	- use ../tests/assignment_files/ as the dir
5) Show userdb at /etc/userdb
6) Show the extended attributes of the assignment files
	- use the command 
			getfattr -d -m ".*" <filename>
7) Show the PAM module on the sysem in /etc/pam.d/system-auth
8) Login with the user daniel graphically
9) Login with alice using su
10) Show the contents of the pseudo-proc directory in /tmp
11) Use Oracle to check daniel's access to each of the files
12) Use Oracle to check alice's access to each of the files
13) Use the file-labeler tool to remove the label extra-access from file2.txt
	sudo ./file-labeler ../data/leveldb ../tests/assignment_files/file2.txt -rc extra-access
14) Show that alice now has access to the file
